  "body": "### Description\r\nAny text of message is editable, only after sending them or typing. If nothing messages are there on UI, means there is nothing to delete or edit or no chat then **Delete chat** option, shouldn't be enable. \r\nType: Feature\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nOption **Delete chat**, this should be enable only when there are any messages/chat. If no messages are there it should be disable.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nBefore sending any messages/chat, Delete chat option is enable & after clicking on that, that contact itself getting deleted.\r\nPlease see the attached screenshot.\r\n![deletechat](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/20433356/33754404-1167a4ba-dc12-11e7-9d91-7da8055abef6.png)\r\n\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n\r\n* Status version: ...0.9.12+\r\n\r\n* Operating System: Android 6.0.1\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n",
