    "body": "@Monali109 Delete chat feature does not delete messages in the chat. It deletes a chat from the list in Chats. Let's say you have 20 chats and want only 5 of them to be shown on Chats tab then you use Delete Chat for the rest of 15 chats. No matter if they contain messages or not. So, the feature works now as expected and deletes a chat.\r\n\r\nRegarding Actual behaviour description:`Before sending any messages/chat, Delete chat option is enable & after clicking on that, that contact itself getting deleted.` Contact can be found on Contacts tab. For example, there is \"Oaken Water Meter\" contact in Contacts. If you open it then new chat \"Oaken Water Meter\" is shown in Chats. If you delete chat with \"Oaken Water Meter\" on Chats then only this chat is deleted. Contact \"Oaken Water Meter\" is still available in Contacts. So all works as expected.\r\n\r\n",
